cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.DB

This paper deals with expertise retrieval and ranking in social networks, which involves analyzing endorsement relations among users. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the use of ranking algorithms such as PageRank, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also deals with data consistency and completeness, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper discusses the use of correlation among skills, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks).
